  "prompt": "What is an interface icon?",
  "response": "An interface icon is a graphical symbol used in digital interfaces to represent actions, objects, files, or operations. These icons serve as visual cues to help users understand and navigate a user interface, such as that of a software application, website, or operating system. \n\nIcons are designed to be simple and intuitive, often resembling the objects or actions they represent to minimize the need for text explanations. For example, a trash bin icon is commonly used to represent the delete function, a gear icon might represent settings, and a magnifying glass icon usually denotes a search feature.\n\nThe primary purpose of interface icons is to enhance usability by making interfaces more visually appealing and easier to navigate, thus improving the overall user experience.",
